  "prompt": "What is the main function of the brachiocephalic artery?",
  "response": "The main function of the brachiocephalic artery, also known as the innominate artery, is to deliver oxygenated blood from the heart to the upper right part of the body. It is one of the major branches off the aortic arch and ultimately supplies blood to the right arm and the right side of the head and neck. After originating from the aortic arch, the brachiocephalic artery divides into the right subclavian artery, which supplies blood to the right arm, and the right common carotid artery, which supplies blood to the right side of the head and neck.",
